{"title": "Chennault's Flying Tigers\n", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chennault%27s_Flying_Tigers", "tags": ["Category:1981 video games", "Category:Apple II games", "Category:Atari 8-bit family games", "Category:Combat flight simulators", "Category:Commodore PET games", "Category:Flying Tigers in fiction", "Category:Game stubs", "Category:Japan in non-Japanese culture", "Category:Short description matches Wikidata", "Category:TRS-80 games", "Category:Video games developed in the United States", "Category:Video games set in China", "Category:Works about the Second Sino-Japanese War", "Category:World War II video games"], "text": "Chennault's Flying Tigers is a 1981 video game published by Discovery Games.\n\nGameplay\nFlying Tigers is a game in which a squadron of P40C Tomahawks battles Japanese pilots in December, 1941. The game is based on the Flying Tigers who flew over China during World War II. The player is tasked with shooting down Japanese bombers and fighters using a keyboard and a joystick.\n\nReception\nDr. Johnny Wilson reviewed the game for Computer Gaming World, and stated that \"In short, Flying Tigers is an interesting game that is not yet living up to its potential.\"\n\n\n== References =="}